1
00:00:03,250 --> 00:00:06,666
- [screaming]

2
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:09,583
[gasping]

3
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:11,750
M--my arm.

4
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:14,500
I still have it, right?

5
00:00:14,583 --> 00:00:16,833
I guess I came back again.

6
00:00:16,916 --> 00:00:18,416
No, wait.

7
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:20,416
Maybe I should say
I made it back.

8
00:00:21,458 --> 00:00:23,500
[both shuddering]

9
00:00:23,583 --> 00:00:26,333
Oh, I'm sorry.
Good morning.

10
00:00:26,416 --> 00:00:27,583
[both shuddering]

11
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:29,041
[grunting]

12
00:00:29,125 --> 00:00:31,625
Right, I guess you don't
remember me, do you?

13
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:33,791
[grunts]

14
00:00:33,875 --> 00:00:35,875
Sorry for the trouble
I've caused till now!

15
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:38,250
Subaru Natsuki
is gonna start over!

16
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,625
both: Huh?
Oh, and what day and time

17
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:43,125
is it right now?

18
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:47,375
<i>[Konomi Suzuki's "Redo"]</i>

19
00:00:47,458 --> 00:00:54,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20
00:00:54,458 --> 00:00:57,375
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

21
00:00:57,458 --> 00:01:04,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:30,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23
00:01:59,333 --> 00:02:06,416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24
00:02:14,625 --> 00:02:17,375
<i>- It's my third first day</i>
<i>in the Roswaal Mansion.</i>

25
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:19,875
That chill I felt,

26
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:22,083
does that mean I died
in my sleep the first time

27
00:02:22,166 --> 00:02:23,541
due to physical weakness?

28
00:02:23,625 --> 00:02:25,875
[distant rattling]
<i>But the second time,</i>

29
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:28,250
there was an attacker.

30
00:02:29,125 --> 00:02:30,541
So if I was killed,

31
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:32,375
does that mean the other folks
here in the mansion

32
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:34,250
were likely targets as well?

33
00:02:34,916 --> 00:02:37,166
<i>'Cause we're involved</i>
<i>in Emilia's royal selection</i>

34
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:38,750
<i>like at the loot house?</i>

35
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,208
But even knowing that,

36
00:02:40,291 --> 00:02:43,458
I've no proof to explain it
or any way to avoid it,

37
00:02:43,541 --> 00:02:45,291
and what makes things worse
is that I didn't get

38
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:46,916
a chance to see
the attacker's face

39
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:48,333
or the other victims.

40
00:02:48,416 --> 00:02:50,208
My death was totally in vain.

41
00:02:50,291 --> 00:02:53,166
- Quit pacing around.
You're really irritating me,

42
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:55,041
so stop or get blown away.

43
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:56,666
- Oh, sorry.

44
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:58,125
It may sound weird,

45
00:02:58,208 --> 00:03:00,166
but walking round in circles
makes the gears in my head

46
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:02,666
turn a lot easier.
Cut me some slack.

47
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:04,000
We're close now,
aren't we?

48
00:03:04,083 --> 00:03:05,791
- Exactly what sort
of relationship

49
00:03:05,875 --> 00:03:07,291
do you think we have,
I suppose?

50
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:09,541
We're not best friends
having only met twice.

51
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,916
- [exhales]

52
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,416
[chuckles]

53
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:15,083
Listen, I'll be out of your hair
as soon as I can, okay?

54
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:17,375
Just serve some tea or something
and let me relax.

55
00:03:17,458 --> 00:03:20,166
- As if I'll serve you anything,
I suppose.

56
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:22,250
[groans]
You are so irritating!

57
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,750
- What's that book
you're reading, anyway?

58
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,583
- It tells how
to get rid of bugs

59
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:28,666
that have gotten into
my room, I suppose.

60
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,583
- Whoa, you've got bugs here
in the library?

61
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:32,458
Man, really sucks for you, huh?

62
00:03:32,541 --> 00:03:34,083
So what kind are they?

63
00:03:34,166 --> 00:03:36,083
- You've long exceeded
your welcome here,

64
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:37,500
so it's time for you to leave.

65
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,583
Your hands have stopped shaking
so you can more easily

66
00:03:39,666 --> 00:03:41,291
disguise your fear now,
I suppose.

67
00:03:41,375 --> 00:03:42,916
- [grunts]
Y--you could tell?

68
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
- You are trying to hide it,
I suppose.

69
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:46,250
It feels rather vexing

70
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:48,458
to be treated
as a mere convenience.

71
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:50,666
- You're not very nice at all,
are you?

72
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,041
Well, thanks for helping me.

73
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,750
I'll see you again soon.

74
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:56,125
- I don't want to see you again,
I suppose.

75
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:58,041
So refrain from coming
in here anymore.

76
00:03:58,125 --> 00:04:00,458
- [grunts]
- Shoo, shoo.

77
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:02,291
- Shoo, shoo?
Really?

78
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,958
[grunts]
Wait a sec.

79
00:04:04,041 --> 00:04:05,666
When you said bugs,
did you mean me?

80
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:06,750
- [grunts]
Just get out

81
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,041
of here this instant!

82
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:10,500
- [groans]
[shouts]

83
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,416
[shouting]

84
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,333
[groaning]

85
00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:16,625
[gasps]

86
00:04:16,708 --> 00:04:18,000
If not for this flower bed,

87
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:19,333
that would have been
instant death.

88
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:20,791
- Um--
- [grunts]

89
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:23,958
- That looked painful.
Are you all right?

90
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:26,666
- Eh?
Of course, Mili.

91
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,208
Your kindness is the one thing
that can heal me.

92
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:30,583
- Just so you know,

93
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,333
Rem spread manure as fertilizer

94
00:04:32,416 --> 00:04:33,875
all over
that flower bed yesterday.

95
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:35,166
- [shouting]

96
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:37,541
The three second rule!
That didn't count!

97
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,166
That didn't count, okay?

98
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:40,666
- You know,
believe it or not,

99
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:42,750
they say this kind of thing
happening to you

100
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,583
is actually sort of lucky.

101
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:48,500
- Mili is already shifting
into consolation mode with me.

102
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:50,958
- [laughs]

103
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:52,541
Hey, Puck, rise and shine.

104
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:56,291
<i>[quirky music]</i>

105
00:04:56,375 --> 00:04:58,000
- [yawns]

106
00:04:58,083 --> 00:05:00,375
Hey there.
Good morning, Lia.

107
00:05:00,458 --> 00:05:02,375
- Good morning to you, Puck.

108
00:05:02,458 --> 00:05:03,625
Sorry to ask this of you

109
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:05,083
being that you only
just woke up,

110
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:07,000
but could you wash off Subaru?

111
00:05:07,083 --> 00:05:08,708
- Wash him off?
- [groans]

112
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:10,166
- Oh, okay.

113
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:11,541
No problem.

114
00:05:11,625 --> 00:05:12,541
- Uh--
- Here!

115
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:16,250
- [shouting]

116
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:18,666
- [laughing]

117
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,333
There you go!
All clean!

118
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:21,500
Not bad, huh?

119
00:05:21,583 --> 00:05:22,541
- [grunts]

120
00:05:22,625 --> 00:05:26,208
[gurgling]

121
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:28,791
I thought I was a goner.

122
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:31,125
Wasn't there some other way
you could have cleaned me up?

123
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:33,333
You enjoyed that,
didn't you?

124
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,041
- That's not true at all,
Subaru.

125
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:37,083
[shouts]
- [gasps]

126
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:38,708
- Oh, yeah?
Take this!

127
00:05:38,791 --> 00:05:40,000
[both grunting]

128
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:41,416
- Oh, now you've done it!

129
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,208
[grunts]
Yeah, you like that?

130
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:45,666
It's my lethal move called,
"Make that cat cry!"

131
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:48,250
- Cut it out!
Tail punch!

132
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,833
- You--
- And I'll finish you off

133
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:51,916
with my bump and grind!

134
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,791
- [laughs]
- Grind, grind, grind, grind!

135
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:58,125
- [laughing]

136
00:05:58,208 --> 00:05:59,458
Oh, my gosh, sorry!

137
00:05:59,541 --> 00:06:01,583
I just can't--
[laughing]

138
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:03,041
What in the world?

139
00:06:03,125 --> 00:06:04,250
What are you--
both: Huh?

140
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,750
What are you two doing?
Oh, my stomach.

141
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:08,291
I'm dying.
[laughing]

142
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:11,250
- Well, I suppose I bounced back
from my initial bad impression.

143
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,583
I do thank you for your
assistance, dear Father.

144
00:06:13,666 --> 00:06:15,208
- Who are you calling Father?

145
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:17,625
I won't give you my daughter
that easily.

146
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:20,166
- Stop that.
You're both too funny.

147
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:21,500
I--
[laughing]

148
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,166
- You've got a great smile, Lia.

149
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:25,250
You agree, don't you, Subaru?

150
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:27,166
- Yes, totally.

151
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:31,375
To me, Mili's lovely smile
is the first shining star

152
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:32,458
in the night sky!

153
00:06:32,541 --> 00:06:34,416
- Aw, come on, Subaru.

154
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:37,041
What did you mean by Mili,
anyway?

155
00:06:37,125 --> 00:06:38,666
Where did that come from?
- Huh?

156
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:39,958
[chuckles]

157
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:41,750
It's what's commonly referred to
as a nickname

158
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:43,166
or a pet name.

159
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,208
Pretty much the same thing
as when Puck calls you Lia.

160
00:06:45,291 --> 00:06:46,583
It's meant to be
a playful expression

161
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:49,291
of affection that shows
two people's closeness.

162
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:52,083
- I see, but that would imply
you and I are close

163
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:54,291
when we hardly know each other.
- [gasps]

164
00:06:54,375 --> 00:06:56,250
You've got a point
and that hurts somewhat,

165
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,833
but I won't lose heart!

166
00:06:57,916 --> 00:07:00,166
Think of it as an advance
in our relationship.

167
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:02,666
It means I want us to get
close enough to call each other

168
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:04,958
by playful pet names, okay?

169
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,000
- [gasps]
- [giggles]

170
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:09,500
- [stammers]

171
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:10,791
A--all right.

172
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:12,791
I suppose I can accept that.

173
00:07:12,875 --> 00:07:14,625
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

174
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,666
No, please,
don't look at me.

175
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:19,083
- I really expected her
to cringe,

176
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:20,750
but I got a positive response.

177
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:23,250
- What could this reaction mean,
commentator Puck?

178
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:25,291
- She doesn't have
very many friends,

179
00:07:25,375 --> 00:07:27,625
so she crave things like
nicknames and being playful.

180
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:29,000
Really easy to please,
you know?

181
00:07:29,083 --> 00:07:31,708
- My main heroine is easy
to please, huh?

182
00:07:31,791 --> 00:07:34,666
- Sister, sister,
it's only been a short time,

183
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,791
and now our guest looks like
a drowned rat.

184
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:39,125
- Rem, Rem,
in just a short time,

185
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,708
our guest has turned into
a dirty old wash rag.

186
00:07:41,791 --> 00:07:43,333
- I know I'm a mess, okay?

187
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,125
I don't need the two of you
to tell me.

188
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:48,541
both: Our lord Master Roswaal
has returned to the premises.

189
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:50,125
Please come inside.

190
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:52,000
- [exhales]

191
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:53,708
Here we go.

192
00:07:53,791 --> 00:07:56,875
My third first meeting
with the lord of the mansion.

193
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:59,875
<i>All I know for certain</i>
<i>in this current loop of events</i>

194
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:03,125
<i>is that somebody is going</i>
<i>to attack on the fourth night.</i>

195
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:05,166
<i>It would be ideal</i>
<i>if I could let them know</i>

196
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:06,375
<i>and warn them,</i>

197
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:07,958
<i>but I wouldn't be able</i>
<i>to explain where</i>

198
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:09,375
<i>I got the information,</i>

199
00:08:09,458 --> 00:08:11,791
<i>so they might think I'm working</i>
<i>with the assassin.</i>

200
00:08:11,875 --> 00:08:14,458
<i>If I knew even as little</i>
<i>as the attacker's physique,</i>

201
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:16,625
<i>it could be a different story.</i>

202
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:18,291
<i>So this time around,</i>

203
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:20,875
<i>I'll use these next four days</i>
<i>to gather as much information</i>

204
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,250
<i>as I can</i>
<i>and find out who it is,</i>

205
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:25,083
<i>and to do that...</i>

206
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:27,541
- You may have any reward
you request.

207
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:31,208
So simply name your desire
and it shall be.

208
00:08:31,291 --> 00:08:32,458
- In that case,

209
00:08:32,541 --> 00:08:35,083
I ask that you let me live here
as a house guest

210
00:08:35,166 --> 00:08:37,291
and eat and sleep
as much as I want.

211
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,375
- [yawns]

212
00:08:41,458 --> 00:08:42,958
[grunts]

213
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,333
- How am I supposed to go

214
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:47,000
about gathering information,
anyway?

215
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,666
Didn't really think
about all that.

216
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:51,250
Guess I'll start off with
some indirect questioning.

217
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,958
[grunting]

218
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:55,500
That's the place where I fell.

219
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:56,458
[grunts]

220
00:08:56,541 --> 00:08:57,833
[birds chirping]

221
00:08:57,916 --> 00:08:59,416
[grunts]

222
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,500
Sorry for all
the trouble I caused.

223
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:02,625
- Don't mention it.

224
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,500
If you'll excuse me, sir.

225
00:09:04,583 --> 00:09:05,791
- Hey, wait.

226
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:08,458
We didn't even get
a chance to talk.

227
00:09:08,541 --> 00:09:11,416
<i>[quirky music]</i>

228
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:13,625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

229
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:16,291
Hmm, nothing out
of the ordinary here.

230
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:18,041
[distant rattling]
[grunts]

231
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:19,833
[chains rattling]

232
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:22,291
- What isn't ordinary?

233
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:23,458
- Ros!

234
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:25,333
Don't sneak up
and scare me like that.

235
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:27,291
It's misleading.
- [chuckles]

236
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:32,750
- [groans]

237
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:35,041
[knocking]
Uh, yes?

238
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:37,541
- Tea time, sir.
Here you are.

239
00:09:37,625 --> 00:09:39,250
- Oh, uh, thanks.

240
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:40,500
Wanna drink it with me?

241
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:42,750
- That's very kind,
but no thank you, sir.

242
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,500
- Uh, hey, you know,

243
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:47,041
if you wanted to be
a little friendlier

244
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:48,708
that'd be fine by me.

245
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:52,916
[grunts]

246
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,083
Well, it is my first day.
Guess that's expected.

247
00:09:58,708 --> 00:09:59,916
Yo.

248
00:10:00,541 --> 00:10:02,708
- You come in here every day
without even knocking.

249
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:05,083
Seems you truly have
no manners whatsoever.

250
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,916
It would be in your
best interest to leave

251
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,416
before you get blown away,
I suppose.

252
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,083
- Whoa, hang on a second!

253
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:11,708
I just wanted
to ask you something.

254
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:12,875
That's all!

255
00:10:12,958 --> 00:10:14,333
Is there any magic
that can weaken

256
00:10:14,416 --> 00:10:15,875
and kill someone but makes it

257
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,500
look like they're
just going to sleep?

258
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:20,583
- If I must answer,
then yes, there is.

259
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:23,083
- Are you serious?

260
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:26,333
- But it's not so much magic
as it is a curse, I suppose.

261
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,875
Actually, there are many
such things among the spells

262
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:31,833
that shamans specialize in.
- So what are shamans?

263
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,375
- Magicians.

264
00:10:33,458 --> 00:10:35,916
Originating in the northern
nation of Gusteco,

265
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,708
they're actually a subclass
of magic and spirit arts users,

266
00:10:38,791 --> 00:10:40,041
I suppose.

267
00:10:40,125 --> 00:10:42,208
They're all quite useless,
to be perfectly honest,

268
00:10:42,291 --> 00:10:44,416
and not to be taken seriously,

269
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,041
but to achieve that result,

270
00:10:46,125 --> 00:10:48,500
there is an easier method
than a curse, I suppose.

271
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:50,041
- There is?

272
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:51,875
- I think you've
already experienced

273
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:53,375
what I'm talking
about firsthand.

274
00:10:53,458 --> 00:10:54,958
- [grunts]

275
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:56,625
Wait, do you mean--

276
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:59,333
<i>That mana drain you did</i>
<i>against my will</i>

277
00:10:59,416 --> 00:11:00,791
<i>could actually kill me?</i>

278
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:02,666
[gasps]

279
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:03,791
- In case you didn't know,

280
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,541
mana is also one's life essence.

281
00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:07,625
If you continually suck it out
by force,

282
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:10,375
one could feasibly die
of weakness, I suppose.

283
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:11,916
- Wait, hold on.

284
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,000
You're not the one
who killed me, are you?

285
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:15,416
- Sorry to disappoint you,

286
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,375
but I'm too busy
for such an endeavor.

287
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:19,791
I couldn't even spare the effort
to kill you.

288
00:11:19,875 --> 00:11:21,875
It's not worth my time.
[grunting]

289
00:11:21,958 --> 00:11:23,916
- This what you're after?

290
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,208
- [grunts]
- Uh, okay.

291
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:30,125
Anyway, can pretty much anyone
do that mana-sucking thing?

292
00:11:30,208 --> 00:11:32,916
- That's an absolutely terrible
way to put it, I suppose.

293
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,666
In this mansion, only Bubby
and I are able to.

294
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:38,083
Even Roswaal is incapable.
- Oh.

295
00:11:38,166 --> 00:11:40,208
Must mean it's actually
a pretty rare skill, then.

296
00:11:40,291 --> 00:11:41,666
Well, now that I know,

297
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,416
don't suck up that stuff
too much,

298
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,541
especially from me.

299
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:45,833
With everything
I've been through,

300
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:46,958
I'd die in an instant.

301
00:11:47,041 --> 00:11:48,250
I'm really short
of blood right now.

302
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:51,125
- Yes, all of your organs
were restored,

303
00:11:51,208 --> 00:11:53,291
but your blood wasn't replaced,
I suppose.

304
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:56,458
Not that I have any obligation
to do such a thing anyway.

305
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:57,875
- My organs?

306
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:01,625
You know, the way you said
all that just now

307
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,958
kinda makes it sound like
you were the one who magically

308
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:06,250
healed my wounds
and saved my life.

309
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:08,208
Trying to take credit
for what Mili did

310
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:09,458
makes you look pretty bad!

311
00:12:09,541 --> 00:12:11,416
- What in the world
are you talking about?

312
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,166
That silly girl doesn't have
the power

313
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:15,208
to heal fatal wounds yet,
I suppose.

314
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,000
- Huh?
- She and Bubby may have

315
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:18,500
stabilized you
and brought you here

316
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:20,625
but I was the one who used magic
to heal you.

317
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:22,583
- Huh?
F--for real?

318
00:12:22,666 --> 00:12:24,083
You're kidding, right?

319
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:25,916
Wait, I get it.

320
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,166
You're lying about
this whole thing, aren't you?

321
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:31,125
It's not nice to lie.
Lying bad!

322
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,666
- Shut up, I suppose.

323
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,333
You're too averse to the truth

324
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:36,583
which means you should
disappear, I suppose!

325
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:39,500
- [grunts]
Whoa!

326
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:41,000
[groaning]

327
00:12:41,083 --> 00:12:43,916
- Uh, once again,
are you all right?

328
00:12:46,583 --> 00:12:48,000
<i>- So in the end,</i>

329
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,041
<i>the keywords</i>
<i>are curse and chains.</i>

330
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:52,458
<i>I don't know anything else.</i>

331
00:12:52,541 --> 00:12:54,958
<i>If the conditions for Return</i>
<i>by Death are the same,</i>

332
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:56,958
<i>I died three times</i>
<i>in the capitol,</i>

333
00:12:57,041 --> 00:12:59,000
<i>and survived the fourth time,</i>

334
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:01,458
<i>but that doesn't mean I intend</i>
<i>to treat this</i>

335
00:13:01,541 --> 00:13:03,000
<i>as a throw away life.</i>

336
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:05,750
<i>That's why I asked Puck</i>
<i>to keep an eye on Emilia for me.</i>

337
00:13:05,833 --> 00:13:07,083
<i>I don't wanna mess this up.</i>

338
00:13:07,166 --> 00:13:08,666
- Yeah, you got it.

339
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:10,500
Everything you're saying
is pretty vague,

340
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:13,166
but I can tell you're asking
out of concern for Lia.

341
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:16,833
<i>- On the morning</i>
<i>of the fourth day,</i>

342
00:13:16,916 --> 00:13:18,333
<i>I'll leave here and--</i>
[knocking]

343
00:13:18,416 --> 00:13:19,500
[grunts]
[door opening]

344
00:13:19,583 --> 00:13:21,500
- Pardon my intrusion, sir.

345
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:23,708
You really are studying, sir.

346
00:13:23,791 --> 00:13:26,000
I'm surprised.
- Surprised, huh?

347
00:13:26,083 --> 00:13:27,875
Well, that's a pretty rude thing
to say.

348
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:29,541
I mean, I am a guest here,
you know.

349
00:13:29,625 --> 00:13:31,958
- You're a freeloader
calling yourself a guest.

350
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:34,041
Least that's how I perceive it,
sir.

351
00:13:34,125 --> 00:13:36,208
Here you go.
- Thanks all the same.

352
00:13:38,541 --> 00:13:39,458
[groans]

353
00:13:39,541 --> 00:13:40,916
It's still nasty.

354
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,916
- Careful.

355
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,125
You're going to incur the wrath

356
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:45,166
of the finest tea leaves
in the mansion.

357
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:48,541
- Slacking off right in front
of your guest?

358
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:50,333
I've no words
for that nerve of yours.

359
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:51,666
Having a seat,
drinking tea.

360
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:53,041
- Well, you were the one
who told me

361
00:13:53,125 --> 00:13:54,541
I should be friendlier,
remember?

362
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,833
So I suppose you could say
I'm only responding

363
00:13:56,916 --> 00:13:58,583
to your demand.
- [grunts]

364
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:01,083
- How's your studying
coming along so far?

365
00:14:01,166 --> 00:14:02,166
- Not bad.

366
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:04,375
I'm able to read
some simple fairy tales

367
00:14:04,458 --> 00:14:05,750
like these now.

368
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,958
It's interesting how
the morals differ just slightly

369
00:14:08,041 --> 00:14:09,250
from the ones I know.

370
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:11,750
It's like true
cross-cultural communication.

371
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,916
Maybe I should import
a few fairy tales

372
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,750
from my homeland
to show you what I mean,

373
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,583
like The Red Ogre Who Cried.
- [gasps]

374
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:18,916
- [grunts]

375
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:22,125
- The Red Ogre Who Cried?

376
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:27,333
- Intrigued, huh?
You want me to tell it to you?

377
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:36,041
Now, you really need
to pay attention, okay?

378
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:38,750
This is how it goes.

379
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:40,625
Once upon a time,

380
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:43,625
there lived a red ogre
and a blue ogre.

381
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:46,750
The two were the best
of friends.

382
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,208
Just inseparable.

383
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:51,916
One day, the red ogre wanted
to be friends

384
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,083
with the people
of the nearby village

385
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:57,375
He approached but the people
were too scared

386
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:58,958
to get close to him.

387
00:14:59,666 --> 00:15:01,875
The blue ogre couldn't bear
to watch this happen

388
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:04,583
so he devised a plan
to help his friend.

389
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:06,750
"I'll make a ruckus
in the village

390
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:08,000
"and frighten everyone.

391
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:10,333
"When I do,
you come and stop me.

392
00:15:10,416 --> 00:15:13,208
After that, the villagers
will be sure to trust you."

393
00:15:13,291 --> 00:15:15,583
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

394
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:17,458
The plan worked,

395
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:18,708
<i>and just as predicted,</i>

396
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:20,625
<i>the red ogre befriended</i>
<i>the humans.</i>

397
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:23,625
<i>But as time passed,</i>

398
00:15:23,708 --> 00:15:26,083
<i>something he noticed began</i>
<i>to worry him.</i>

399
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:29,583
<i>His friend,</i>
<i>the blue ogre,</i>

400
00:15:29,666 --> 00:15:31,666
<i>no longer stopped by to visit.</i>

401
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:34,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

402
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:38,500
One day, the red ogre decided
to go to the blue ogre's house.

403
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:39,625
Abandoned.

404
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:41,333
The shades were drawn
in the windows,

405
00:15:41,416 --> 00:15:43,458
and the door was shut
and locked.

406
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:46,791
There was a letter attached
to the door that said...

407
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:50,166
"Red Ogre,

408
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:53,791
please have fun with your new
human friends and companions."

409
00:15:55,083 --> 00:15:56,750
"If I continue
to hang around you,

410
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:59,666
"I'm afraid they might think
you're a bad ogre, too,

411
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,375
and end the friendship
you sought from them."

412
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:05,166
"Thus..."

413
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:09,041
"I've decided
to go on a journey.

414
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:12,916
I'm not sure I'll return,
but I will never forget you."

415
00:16:14,458 --> 00:16:16,458
"Good-bye.

416
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:18,875
"Take care of yourself.

417
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:22,083
"Your friend now and forever,

418
00:16:22,166 --> 00:16:23,708
Blue Ogre."

419
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:29,375
The red ogre red the letter
in silence over and over.

420
00:16:29,458 --> 00:16:32,500
He began to cry and the tears
welled up in his eyes.

421
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:34,875
That's the end.

422
00:16:34,958 --> 00:16:39,083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

423
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,500
- That's a sad story.

424
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:44,083
- Yeah, it is.

425
00:16:44,166 --> 00:16:45,750
But even with
an ending like that,

426
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:47,875
I think it's kind of
a sweet story also.

427
00:16:47,958 --> 00:16:49,875
- If you ask me,

428
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:52,250
all the characters in it
are just stupid.

429
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:54,166
The red ogre,
the blue ogre,

430
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:55,583
and the villagers, too.

431
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:58,458
- Wow, that's a pretty harsh
critique, don't you think?

432
00:16:58,541 --> 00:17:00,708
I mean, sure,
I'm not denying it,

433
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:03,291
but that's probably
the reason why I both love

434
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:05,416
and hate that story, honestly.

435
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:09,041
The blue ogre's self sacrifice
is really appealing,

436
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:11,791
but it's stupid because
he gets nothing out of it.

437
00:17:11,875 --> 00:17:14,083
I'm the type that wants
to be rewarded for the effort

438
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:15,125
I put in.

439
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:16,750
- Is that really what you think

440
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,958
about the blue ogre?

441
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:21,916
To me it's the red ogre
that I feel is beyond help

442
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:25,083
He dragged the blue ogre
into his own desires

443
00:17:25,166 --> 00:17:27,333
and as a result,
he lost nothing.

444
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:29,458
Only the blue ogre
lost anything.

445
00:17:29,541 --> 00:17:30,958
- Interesting point.

446
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:33,708
Then what do you think the two
of them should have done?

447
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:36,250
- If the red ogre truly wanted
to become friends

448
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,708
with the humans in the village,

449
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,500
he should have broken off
his horns and gone to them.

450
00:17:41,208 --> 00:17:43,083
If he had done that
from the very beginning,

451
00:17:43,166 --> 00:17:44,916
the blue ogre might have stayed.

452
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,708
- I--I think you're missing
the point.

453
00:17:46,791 --> 00:17:48,375
That's a pretty extreme opinion.

454
00:17:48,458 --> 00:17:49,750
- You really think so?

455
00:17:49,833 --> 00:17:51,166
Answer this.

456
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:53,875
Which of the two ogres would you
rather be friends with?

457
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:55,583
- Which of the two?

458
00:17:57,458 --> 00:17:59,125
- The red ogre who could
only wish

459
00:17:59,208 --> 00:18:00,708
to be taken care of by others,

460
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:03,666
or the blue ogre basking
in his own self sacrifice?

461
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,583
- [exhales]

462
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:10,000
<i>[soft guitar music]</i>

463
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:11,500
- [grunts]

464
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:14,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

465
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:16,375
What a boring answer.

466
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:18,250
If you want to befriend both
of them,

467
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:20,083
I can only conclude
that you must be

468
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:21,916
the indecisive adulteress type.

469
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,166
You'll regret it one day.

470
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,583
- How can you say that?

471
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:26,666
I don't recall it being
that kind of story.

472
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:29,583
- Putting aside the questionable
fairy tales of your homeland,

473
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:32,375
did any of these stories leave
an impression on you?

474
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:34,125
- Well, let's see.

475
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:36,708
The ones that interested me most
were the one in the middle

476
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:38,750
about the dragon
and the one at the end

477
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:40,166
about the witch.

478
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:41,958
I finally know where the name

479
00:18:42,041 --> 00:18:44,291
Dragon's Kingdom of Lugunica
came from.

480
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:45,666
- Oh?

481
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,833
- It said the royal family
designed a covenant

482
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:49,875
with a dragon
so it's more a folk tale

483
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:51,666
than a fairy tale,
wouldn't you say?

484
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:54,291
- Yes, I would,
since it's true.

485
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:57,708
The noble dragon lives far away
beyond a great waterfall.

486
00:18:57,791 --> 00:18:59,416
But even with that distance,

487
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:01,916
the dragon still upholds
its duty to protect us.

488
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,250
It was in the royal
family's contract

489
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,000
and must be honored
till it's fulfilled.

490
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:07,416
- Wait a sec.

491
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,583
The royal family that has
the contract with the dragon,

492
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:11,541
didn't they die out recently?

493
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:13,708
- They did.
Rather abruptly at that.

494
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:17,541
No one's sure what the noble
dragon wants to do now.

495
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:19,458
In the nation's
current situation,

496
00:19:19,541 --> 00:19:21,708
I imagine only the gods
are aware.

497
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:25,000
No, at this point,
only the dragon knows.

498
00:19:25,083 --> 00:19:26,875
- Hmm.

499
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:28,375
Oh, by the way,

500
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:31,791
about this witch story.
- I don't wanna discuss that.

501
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:33,625
- Uh--
- I've stayed here far too long.

502
00:19:33,708 --> 00:19:35,458
When dinner has been prepared,

503
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:37,583
I will stop by
to notify you, sir.

504
00:19:39,291 --> 00:19:41,583
- Oh, okay.
[door opens]

505
00:19:41,666 --> 00:19:43,250
- Do me a favor.

506
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:45,125
That story you told me
about the ogres,

507
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:46,500
don't tell it to Rem.

508
00:19:46,583 --> 00:19:48,750
I'm certain that she wouldn't
like it very much.

509
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,500
- [grunts]

510
00:19:57,250 --> 00:20:00,250
A scary witch.
A truly terrifying witch.

511
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:03,500
To even speak her name
would chill you to the bone.

512
00:20:03,583 --> 00:20:08,000
Everybody referred to her
as the Witch of Envy.

513
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:14,666
- Are you sure about this?

514
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:16,125
We could call a dragon-drawn
carriage

515
00:20:16,208 --> 00:20:18,125
to take you to the capitol.
It's no trouble.

516
00:20:18,208 --> 00:20:19,541
- Thank you but I'll be fine.

517
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:21,291
And one day when
I finally become

518
00:20:21,375 --> 00:20:24,291
the kind of strong, smart,
rich man who's worthy of you,

519
00:20:24,375 --> 00:20:25,708
I'll come to you on
a white horse

520
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:27,208
to take you away with me.

521
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:28,541
- Do you have a handkerchief?

522
00:20:28,625 --> 00:20:30,458
And water,
and plenty of lagumite ore?

523
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:32,958
Let's see, and will you be able
to sleep by yourself?

524
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:34,625
- Do you think you're my mom?

525
00:20:34,708 --> 00:20:36,583
- Safe travels to you, Subaru.

526
00:20:36,666 --> 00:20:37,791
I wish you well.

527
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:40,000
And don't lose
the gift I gave you.

528
00:20:40,083 --> 00:20:42,083
As an attempt to equate our
three days worth

529
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:43,291
of memories together,

530
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:45,333
I gave you a little something.
- [grunts]

531
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:47,583
Oh, hush money, right?

532
00:20:47,666 --> 00:20:48,791
Don't worry.
I get it.

533
00:20:48,875 --> 00:20:50,333
I won't say anything
I shouldn't.

534
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:51,750
I swear to the dragon.

535
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,666
- Oh, just talking with you
makes any evil scheme

536
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,666
seem to lose its purpose.

537
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:58,666
And in case you didn't know,
in this nation,

538
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:01,333
swearing to the dragon
is the highest form of promise.

539
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:04,083
Make sure you never forget it,
okay?

540
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:05,916
- You got it!

541
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,166
The two of you helped
me out so much.

542
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,833
Especially you, Rem-Rem.

543
00:21:09,916 --> 00:21:11,125
Thanks for all the great food.

544
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:13,833
And Ram, you--oh.

545
00:21:13,916 --> 00:21:15,958
Yeah, you're really good
at cleaning toilets.

546
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:18,125
- Sister, sister,
what a shame.

547
00:21:18,208 --> 00:21:20,041
Our guest is hopelessly bad
at flattery.

548
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:22,083
- Rem, Rem, what a shame.

549
00:21:22,166 --> 00:21:24,083
Our guest has a fatal lack
of flattery skills.

550
00:21:24,166 --> 00:21:25,416
- Oh, shut up!

551
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:27,250
I seriously couldn't think
of anything to say, okay?

552
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:30,125
Thanks, though.
I appreciate it.

553
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:31,958
both: Yes, sir.

554
00:21:37,208 --> 00:21:38,458
- [grunts]

555
00:21:38,541 --> 00:21:40,083
- Subaru?
- [grunts]

556
00:21:40,625 --> 00:21:42,041
- Thanks for all you've done.

557
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:44,500
If you're ever in need,
come visit us any time.

558
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:47,041
- Will do.

559
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:49,000
- [giggling]

560
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:51,750
- Thanks a bunch, Mili!

561
00:21:57,958 --> 00:22:00,166
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

562
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:01,791
[grunts]

563
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:03,791
[panting]

564
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:10,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

565
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:13,958
Okay, this is it.

566
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:16,875
I've got a good view
of Emilia's room.

567
00:22:17,541 --> 00:22:21,833
And now I'll just wait around
for something to happen,

568
00:22:21,916 --> 00:22:23,625
then stop it.

569
00:22:26,333 --> 00:22:29,500
Rem-Rem would probably get mad
at me for using it like this.

570
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:32,708
I hope she does, anyway.

571
00:22:34,416 --> 00:22:36,916
I don't wanna die again.

572
00:22:38,833 --> 00:22:40,833
I don't want them
to die, either.

573
00:22:44,125 --> 00:22:46,708
Now, what did I tell you,
Subaru Natsuki?

574
00:22:47,166 --> 00:22:49,250
Even if no one remembers
anything that happened

575
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:50,958
when everything repeats,

576
00:22:51,041 --> 00:22:52,958
you remember it clear as day.

577
00:22:57,208 --> 00:22:59,291
Uh, now that I really think
about it,

578
00:22:59,375 --> 00:23:01,291
I didn't go shopping
with Rem this time.

579
00:23:01,875 --> 00:23:04,541
Just because the food meant
for me was left over.

580
00:23:06,416 --> 00:23:08,916
<i>It'll still be a while before</i>
<i>it gets dark.</i>

581
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,958
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>Focus, focus.</i>

582
00:23:11,041 --> 00:23:12,375
[snarling]
[grunts]

583
00:23:12,458 --> 00:23:13,791
[snarling]
[gasps]

584
00:23:13,875 --> 00:23:15,500
[shouts]

585
00:23:18,041 --> 00:23:19,500
[grunts]

586
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:23,125
[grunts]

587
00:23:23,208 --> 00:23:25,000
Emergency escape!

588
00:23:25,083 --> 00:23:26,541
[grunts]
I saw it.

589
00:23:26,625 --> 00:23:27,833
Yes, I saw it!

590
00:23:27,916 --> 00:23:30,208
I saw where the sound
of chains came from!

591
00:23:30,291 --> 00:23:32,458
What is it?
Coming this way?

592
00:23:32,541 --> 00:23:34,916
[breathing heavily]

593
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,125
[gasping]

594
00:23:37,208 --> 00:23:38,791
<i>Nowhere to run.</i>

595
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:41,375
<i>Does this mean I played right</i>
<i>into the attacker's hands?</i>

596
00:23:41,458 --> 00:23:45,083
<i>[tense music]</i>

597
00:23:45,166 --> 00:23:47,791
[grunts]

598
00:23:47,875 --> 00:23:49,791
If you're coming,
then come.

599
00:23:49,875 --> 00:23:56,458
[chains rattling]

600
00:23:56,541 --> 00:23:59,333
Now, don't you have the nerve
to face me?

601
00:23:59,416 --> 00:24:00,583
[grunts]

602
00:24:00,666 --> 00:24:02,250
[screams]

603
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:03,375
[grunts]

604
00:24:03,458 --> 00:24:05,916
All right, show yourself,
you damn coward!

605
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,958
I've gone through hell trying
to see your face,

606
00:24:08,041 --> 00:24:10,250
so come out!

607
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:11,916
[grunts]

608
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:17,333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

609
00:24:17,416 --> 00:24:18,625
[grunts]

610
00:24:18,708 --> 00:24:24,666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

611
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:26,208
- Then I have no choice.

612
00:24:26,291 --> 00:24:28,166
- [gasps]

613
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:33,208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

614
00:24:33,291 --> 00:24:35,208
[gasping]

615
00:24:35,291 --> 00:24:38,208
- The ideal scenario would
have been to finish this

616
00:24:38,291 --> 00:24:40,208
without anyone noticing.

617
00:24:40,291 --> 00:24:42,166
- [gasps]

618
00:24:42,250 --> 00:24:44,125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

619
00:24:44,208 --> 00:24:45,625
[winces]

620
00:24:45,708 --> 00:24:47,458
You're joking.

621
00:24:47,541 --> 00:24:49,083
Right, Rem?

622
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:06,375
- As long as you do not resist,

623
00:25:06,458 --> 00:25:09,416
I can make your death
a painless one.

624
00:25:09,500 --> 00:25:11,916
- Why?
Why are you doing this?

625
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,916
Look, might be a cliché to ask,
but I gotta know.

626
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,083
- It's simply the rule of maids.

627
00:25:17,166 --> 00:25:19,125
If someone's suspicious,
punish them.

628
00:25:20,166 --> 00:25:21,875
- Tell me.
Does Ram know, too?

629
00:25:21,958 --> 00:25:26,583
- I intend to finish this
before my sister sees anything.

630
00:25:26,666 --> 00:25:30,833
- Is that--is that how little
you trusted me?

631
00:25:31,916 --> 00:25:32,916
- Yes.

632
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,333
- [gasps]

633
00:25:34,416 --> 00:25:36,791
Damn, I'm so pathetic.

634
00:25:36,875 --> 00:25:39,541
And I was so sure that we
were getting along well.

635
00:25:41,208 --> 00:25:42,750
- My sister--
- I don't wanna hear it!

636
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:44,416
Take this!

637
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,833
[camera shutter flashing]

638
00:25:46,916 --> 00:25:49,625
[grunting]

639
00:25:53,041 --> 00:25:56,083
[breathing heavily]

640
00:26:02,375 --> 00:26:03,291
[blow lands]
[gasps]

641
00:26:03,375 --> 00:26:04,541
[shouts]

642
00:26:04,625 --> 00:26:07,666
[groaning]

643
00:26:09,333 --> 00:26:13,541
[shouting]

644
00:26:13,625 --> 00:26:15,416
My leg!

645
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:22,375
[screaming]

646
00:26:22,458 --> 00:26:25,250
- Mana of water,
heal this damaged body.

647
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:29,083
If I let you die too quickly,

648
00:26:29,166 --> 00:26:31,541
then I won't be able to get
any information out of you.

649
00:26:31,625 --> 00:26:33,166
- [whimpers]

650
00:26:37,083 --> 00:26:38,916
- If you had stopped me
with this,

651
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:42,500
you would have been able
to flee a bit further.

652
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:48,166
I ask you this.

653
00:26:48,250 --> 00:26:50,333
Are you a faction member
supporting one

654
00:26:50,416 --> 00:26:52,666
of Miss Emilia's rivals
for the throne?

655
00:26:53,708 --> 00:26:55,583
- My heart belongs
to Mili forever

656
00:26:55,666 --> 00:26:58,250
until the end of t--
[screams]

657
00:26:58,333 --> 00:27:00,083
- Answer me.
Who hired you?

658
00:27:00,166 --> 00:27:01,791
And under what conditions?

659
00:27:01,875 --> 00:27:05,166
- Mili's smile did
and it was priceless.

660
00:27:05,250 --> 00:27:08,708
[screaming]

661
00:27:08,791 --> 00:27:10,375
- Let's try again.

662
00:27:10,458 --> 00:27:13,208
Are you affiliated
with the Witch's Cult?

663
00:27:13,291 --> 00:27:15,416
- The Witch's Cult?

664
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:17,000
[whimpering]

665
00:27:17,083 --> 00:27:18,333
I don't know what that is.

666
00:27:18,416 --> 00:27:20,500
My family's been secular
for generations.

667
00:27:20,583 --> 00:27:22,708
Why--
- Don't you play dumb with me!

668
00:27:22,791 --> 00:27:25,583
Your bald-faced lies can only
take you so far

669
00:27:25,666 --> 00:27:27,375
when the fowl stench
of the witch

670
00:27:27,458 --> 00:27:28,708
is covering you
from head to toe!

671
00:27:28,791 --> 00:27:30,416
- [whimpering]

672
00:27:30,500 --> 00:27:33,541
- Every time I watched you
conversing with my sister,

673
00:27:33,625 --> 00:27:35,500
I felt as if I would go out
of my mind

674
00:27:35,583 --> 00:27:38,041
with anger and unrest.

675
00:27:38,125 --> 00:27:40,875
Someone associated with the one
who has caused my sister

676
00:27:40,958 --> 00:27:43,458
so much agony having
the audacity

677
00:27:43,541 --> 00:27:46,375
to boldly encroach on the place
in which she and I belong.

678
00:27:46,458 --> 00:27:47,875
- [whimpering]

679
00:27:47,958 --> 00:27:50,000
- I can't bear it any longer.

680
00:27:50,083 --> 00:27:53,041
Even if I know deep down
my sister only acts friendly

681
00:27:53,125 --> 00:27:56,083
with you and only pretends
to care for you!

682
00:27:56,166 --> 00:27:59,541
- [whimpering]

683
00:27:59,625 --> 00:28:02,500
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

684
00:28:02,583 --> 00:28:04,333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

685
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:09,375
Look, I don't cut my hands
when I peel vegetables anymore.

686
00:28:09,458 --> 00:28:11,083
- Huh?

687
00:28:11,166 --> 00:28:14,166
- I can read and I can
even write now, too.

688
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:16,250
Just the basics, but hey.

689
00:28:16,333 --> 00:28:19,250
I kept my word
and I studied hard.

690
00:28:19,333 --> 00:28:22,416
I can read those fairy tales.

691
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:24,250
All thanks to you two.

692
00:28:24,333 --> 00:28:26,416
- Fairy tales?
What are you talking about?

693
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:29,666
- I'm talking about all
the wonderful things

694
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:31,333
you guys gave me.

695
00:28:33,041 --> 00:28:35,291
- I have no memory
of any of that.

696
00:28:35,375 --> 00:28:37,958
- [crying]

697
00:28:38,041 --> 00:28:39,375
Why?

698
00:28:39,458 --> 00:28:41,375
Why don't you remember?

699
00:28:41,458 --> 00:28:44,791
Why do all you you keep leaving
me behind like this?

700
00:28:44,875 --> 00:28:46,625
What did I ever do to you?

701
00:28:46,708 --> 00:28:48,458
What am I supposed to do?

702
00:28:48,541 --> 00:28:50,458
What did I do wrong?

703
00:28:50,541 --> 00:28:51,833
I don't understand!

704
00:28:51,916 --> 00:28:54,291
Why do you guys hate me so much?

705
00:28:54,375 --> 00:28:57,125
[crying]

706
00:28:57,208 --> 00:28:59,250
Even when you said
you'd cut my hair...

707
00:28:59,333 --> 00:29:00,750
[crying]

708
00:29:00,833 --> 00:29:03,166
All that time, I...

709
00:29:04,166 --> 00:29:05,583
- I--

710
00:29:05,666 --> 00:29:07,750
- I really like you both!
You--

711
00:29:12,166 --> 00:29:14,208
- [shuddering]

712
00:29:14,916 --> 00:29:17,166
My sister is too kind.

713
00:29:21,916 --> 00:29:23,750
- [gasps]

714
00:29:23,833 --> 00:29:25,041
[groans]

715
00:29:25,125 --> 00:29:27,958
[birds chirping]

716
00:29:28,041 --> 00:29:30,500
- Sir, have you awakened?
- Huh?

717
00:29:30,583 --> 00:29:32,500
- Sir, you're awake?

718
00:29:32,583 --> 00:29:35,625
- [breathing heavily]

719
00:29:36,541 --> 00:29:38,250
[screams]

720
00:29:40,166 --> 00:29:42,666
- Subaru, what was that
all about?

721
00:29:42,750 --> 00:29:44,666
Ram and Rem were really worried.

722
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:46,333
They were unusually despondent

723
00:29:46,416 --> 00:29:47,958
wondering if they'd
been impolite.

724
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:51,625
- Don't worry about it.

725
00:29:51,708 --> 00:29:54,375
Nothing happened between them
and me.

726
00:29:54,458 --> 00:29:56,791
- Subaru, are you all right?

727
00:29:56,875 --> 00:29:58,208
'Cause if something's
troubling you,

728
00:29:58,291 --> 00:30:00,458
you're welcome to talk
to me about it.

729
00:30:00,875 --> 00:30:03,375
<i>- If I could tell Emilia</i>
<i>that it's no use,</i>

730
00:30:03,458 --> 00:30:05,083
<i>that I can't take anymore...</i>

731
00:30:06,125 --> 00:30:07,458
[gasps]
Wait.

732
00:30:07,541 --> 00:30:08,916
That's it.
- What?

733
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,958
<i>- All this time</i>
<i>I've been struggling</i>

734
00:30:11,041 --> 00:30:12,416
<i>to change things alone,</i>

735
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:14,333
<i>but what if--</i>
- Subaru,

736
00:30:14,416 --> 00:30:16,791
are you sure you're okay?

737
00:30:17,750 --> 00:30:19,833
- There's something important
I want to tell you.

738
00:30:19,916 --> 00:30:21,291
- [gasps]

739
00:30:21,375 --> 00:30:22,833
Yes?

740
00:30:22,916 --> 00:30:25,958
- Emilia, several 8times
up until now,

741
00:30:26,041 --> 00:30:28,125
believe it or not,
I've die--

742
00:30:33,666 --> 00:30:36,666
<i>[tense music]</i>

743
00:30:36,750 --> 00:30:43,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

744
00:30:48,166 --> 00:30:51,208
[gasping]

745
00:30:51,291 --> 00:30:53,791
<i>Whoa, wait.</i>

746
00:30:54,958 --> 00:30:57,333
<i>This is seriously no joke.</i>

747
00:30:57,416 --> 00:30:59,333
<i>What's happening?</i>

748
00:30:59,416 --> 00:31:01,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

749
00:31:01,958 --> 00:31:03,666
- What is it?

750
00:31:03,750 --> 00:31:05,625
- [gasping]
- Subaru!

751
00:31:05,708 --> 00:31:07,333
What happened all of a sudden?

752
00:31:07,416 --> 00:31:11,250
- [breathing heavily]

753
00:31:12,750 --> 00:31:15,500
<i>My body moves.</i>
<i>My voice works.</i>

754
00:31:15,583 --> 00:31:17,291
<i>My heart doesn't hurt.</i>

755
00:31:17,375 --> 00:31:18,833
<i>But...</i>

756
00:31:21,041 --> 00:31:23,791
<i>The fear is engraved in me.</i>

757
00:31:23,875 --> 00:31:25,458
- Wh--what's wrong?

758
00:31:25,541 --> 00:31:27,375
You've been acting
really strange.

759
00:31:27,458 --> 00:31:29,458
Tell me.
If something's going on--

760
00:31:29,541 --> 00:31:31,083
