<i>where I died.</i>

1018
00:42:44,708 --> 00:42:46,625
Is this it?

1019
00:42:46,708 --> 00:42:49,041
[breathing heavily]

1020
00:42:49,125 --> 00:42:50,791
If I die...

1021
00:42:50,875 --> 00:42:53,625
<i>- Will I be saved</i>
<i>from this whole situation?</i>

1022
00:42:54,583 --> 00:42:55,875
Of course.

1023
00:42:55,958 --> 00:42:59,125
If I do,
everything will change

1024
00:42:59,208 --> 00:43:03,083
<i>If I struggled and fought</i>
<i>so much only to end up here,</i>

1025
00:43:03,166 --> 00:43:05,458
<i>then what's the point?</i>

1026
00:43:05,541 --> 00:43:06,958
[gasps]

1027
00:43:07,666 --> 00:43:09,583
The cliff.

1028
00:43:09,666 --> 00:43:16,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1029
00:43:17,916 --> 00:43:21,541
[shuddering]

1030
00:43:21,625 --> 00:43:24,250
<i>If I close my eyes</i>
<i>and take one step,</i>

1031
00:43:24,333 --> 00:43:25,666
<i>it'll all be over.</i>

1032
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:27,750
[whimpers]

1033
00:43:27,833 --> 00:43:29,625
<i>What will happen to me</i>

1034
00:43:29,708 --> 00:43:31,125
<i>if I die again?</i>

1035
00:43:31,208 --> 00:43:32,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1036
00:43:32,833 --> 00:43:35,833
[crying]

1037
00:43:42,791 --> 00:43:44,833
It's just one more step.

1038
00:43:44,916 --> 00:43:47,625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1039
00:43:47,708 --> 00:43:49,416
I can't even...

1040
00:43:50,791 --> 00:43:53,625
do something as simple as that.

1041
00:43:55,291 --> 00:43:58,333
[wind blowing]

1042
00:44:03,875 --> 00:44:05,916
<i>- I finally found you.</i>

1043
00:44:10,291 --> 00:44:11,666
- Why?

1044
00:44:11,750 --> 00:44:13,500
- What's the matter,
I suppose?

1045
00:44:13,583 --> 00:44:15,583
- Why did you come out here
for me?

1046
00:44:15,666 --> 00:44:16,791
Didn't I--

1047
00:44:16,875 --> 00:44:18,166
- How quickly you forget.

1048
00:44:18,250 --> 00:44:20,875
The contract I entered into
was to protect you.

1049
00:44:21,958 --> 00:44:23,500
- You're still my bodyguard?

1050
00:44:23,583 --> 00:44:26,250
I thought you were only supposed
to do that until this morning.

1051
00:44:26,333 --> 00:44:29,500
- In that case,
you must be mistaken, I suppose.

1052
00:44:29,583 --> 00:44:32,083
I don't remember discussing
there being a time limit.

1053
00:44:32,166 --> 00:44:33,791
- [shudders]

1054
00:44:34,458 --> 00:44:36,875
- Clinging to faint hope just
serves your own convenience,

1055
00:44:36,958 --> 00:44:38,500
I suppose.
- [grunts]

1056
00:44:38,583 --> 00:44:40,666
- What was lost
can't be reclaimed.

1057
00:44:41,166 --> 00:44:43,458
You'll have no more chances
to explain yourself

1058
00:44:43,541 --> 00:44:44,750
to the older sister.

1059
00:44:44,833 --> 00:44:47,166
That opportunity
has come and gone.

1060
00:44:47,250 --> 00:44:48,875
No matter which is lost,

1061
00:44:48,958 --> 00:44:51,375
they'll never be complete again,
I suppose.

1062
00:44:51,833 --> 00:44:54,708
- But I really cared
about those two very much

1063
00:44:54,791 --> 00:44:56,375
and I wanted to do whatever
I could

1064
00:44:56,458 --> 00:44:58,041
to protect them.
- Why?

1065
00:44:58,125 --> 00:45:00,250
What do you know about them,
I suppose?

1066
00:45:00,333 --> 00:45:02,750
Either way, they'll never
be restored to what

1067
00:45:02,833 --> 00:45:05,916
they once were.
They can't be.

1068
00:45:07,083 --> 00:45:08,833
- So in the end,

1069
00:45:08,916 --> 00:45:11,125
what I was really doing
was making a selfish,

1070
00:45:11,208 --> 00:45:12,875
disgraceful fuss
without actually

1071
00:45:12,958 --> 00:45:14,416
knowing anything at all.

1072
00:45:15,250 --> 00:45:16,583
- At the very least,

1073
00:45:16,666 --> 00:45:18,625
you need to die
where I can't see you

1074
00:45:18,708 --> 00:45:20,875
or I'll just have bad dreams,
I suppose.

1075
00:45:21,625 --> 00:45:25,375
So I'll do what I can to help
you escape this territory.

1076
00:45:28,375 --> 00:45:30,583
<i>[tense music]</i>

1077
00:45:31,625 --> 00:45:32,750
- Huh?

1078
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:35,916
[grunts]

1079
00:45:38,041 --> 00:45:39,875
Come to think of it,
back then,

1080
00:45:39,958 --> 00:45:43,125
somebody was holding both
of my hands.

1081
00:45:43,208 --> 00:45:46,208
<i>[tense music]</i>

1082
00:45:46,291 --> 00:45:47,583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1083
00:45:47,666 --> 00:45:49,708
<i>Ram, Rem.</i>

1084
00:45:49,791 --> 00:45:51,791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1085
00:45:51,875 --> 00:45:54,958
If they couldn't bear to see me
suffering and in pain,

1086
00:45:55,041 --> 00:45:56,958
and they held both my hands,

1087
00:45:57,041 --> 00:45:58,250
<i>- ♪ For my love... ♪</i>

1088
00:45:58,333 --> 00:46:00,333
- If that's the kind
of people they are,

1089
00:46:00,416 --> 00:46:02,625
how can I leave them?

1090
00:46:02,708 --> 00:46:06,500
<i>- I'm going to kill you!</i>

1091
00:46:06,583 --> 00:46:09,500
<i>- I heard a voice filled</i>
<i>with hatred.</i>

1092
00:46:09,583 --> 00:46:11,125
<i>But more than that...</i>

1093
00:46:11,208 --> 00:46:14,375
- [screams]

1094
00:46:14,458 --> 00:46:16,250
<i>- Her cries were haunting.</i>

1095
00:46:16,333 --> 00:46:17,750
<i>They won't leave my mind.</i>

1096
00:46:17,833 --> 00:46:20,333
<i>[MYTH&ROID's "STRAIGHT BET"]</i>

1097
00:46:20,416 --> 00:46:22,000
<i>- ♪ Now have a seat... ♪</i>

1098
00:46:22,083 --> 00:46:25,625
<i>- All my life I've always been</i>
<i>the type to drift toward</i>

1099
00:46:25,708 --> 00:46:27,500
<i>whichever path was easiest.</i>

1100
00:46:27,583 --> 00:46:31,000
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

1101
00:46:31,083 --> 00:46:32,791
- Hey, Subaru.

1102
00:46:32,875 --> 00:46:36,250
You're thinking of something
pretty stupid here.

1103
00:46:36,333 --> 00:46:38,250
And after all that
I went through

1104
00:46:38,333 --> 00:46:39,500
to save this life...

1105
00:46:39,583 --> 00:46:42,500
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

1106
00:46:42,583 --> 00:46:43,916
- That's right.

1107
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,500
I simply saved my own life.
So then--

1108
00:46:46,583 --> 00:46:48,958
<i>What's wrong with taking</i>
<i>the path that's easiest?</i>

1109
00:46:49,041 --> 00:46:51,041
<i>That will let me live longer?</i>

1110
00:46:51,125 --> 00:46:54,958
<i>I'll decide how I use my life!</i>

1111
00:46:55,041 --> 00:46:56,416
- [gasps]

1112
00:46:56,500 --> 00:46:59,000
Afraid you were a bit too slow.

1113
00:46:59,083 --> 00:47:02,291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1114
00:47:02,375 --> 00:47:04,833
- I finally found you.

1115
00:47:04,916 --> 00:47:07,125
I'm not gonna let you get away.

1116
00:47:07,208 --> 00:47:08,583
- Stay back, I suppose.

1117
00:47:08,666 --> 00:47:10,416
So long as my contract exists,

1118
00:47:10,500 --> 00:47:13,083
I won't hold back,
not even against you.

1119
00:47:13,166 --> 00:47:14,791
- And you, Miss Beatrice,

1120
00:47:14,875 --> 00:47:17,541
you seem to have forgotten
we're not in the mansion now.

1121
00:47:17,625 --> 00:47:20,583
We're in the forest away
from the Forbidden Library.

1122
00:47:20,666 --> 00:47:23,875
Are you so certain that you'll
be able to protect him from me?

1123
00:47:23,958 --> 00:47:27,333
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

1124
00:47:27,416 --> 00:47:30,916
- [grunts]
- [laughs]

1125
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:32,500
Pow.
Hmm.

1126
00:47:32,583 --> 00:47:34,208
Oh, yeah.
That feels good.

1127
00:47:34,291 --> 00:47:36,250
- [snarling]

1128
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:38,291
What are you doing,
you buffoon?

1129
00:47:38,375 --> 00:47:39,750
Do you want to die or something?

1130
00:47:39,833 --> 00:47:41,500
- Of course not.
Don't be dumb.

1131
00:47:41,583 --> 00:47:43,416
That isn't what I want at all.

1132
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:47,208
I only wanna die once at the end
of a long and happy life.

1133
00:47:47,291 --> 00:47:48,916
That's how I really feel.

1134
00:47:50,125 --> 00:47:51,333
- You've got guts.

1135
00:47:51,416 --> 00:47:53,750
So you finally accept your fate?

1136
00:47:53,833 --> 00:47:56,083
- That's not a very
accurate description.

1137
00:47:56,166 --> 00:47:59,041
If anything,
I would say that now

1138
00:47:59,125 --> 00:48:00,708
I've made up my mind.

1139
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:03,208
Sorry.

1140
00:48:03,291 --> 00:48:04,916
I caused a lot of grief
for you guys

1141
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:06,625
by being such
a pathetic loser.

1142
00:48:06,708 --> 00:48:07,750
- [gasps]

1143
00:48:07,833 --> 00:48:09,750
So you do know something
about Rem!

1144
00:48:09,833 --> 00:48:12,458
- Nope, sorry, but I honestly
don't know a thing.

1145
00:48:12,541 --> 00:48:14,416
Frankly, there's too much
I don't know.

1146
00:48:14,500 --> 00:48:17,958
Even so, I decided to learn more
about the things

1147
00:48:18,041 --> 00:48:20,625
I don't understand
and to not be in the dark.

1148
00:48:20,708 --> 00:48:22,291
- How can you possibly say that?

1149
00:48:22,375 --> 00:48:24,333
My sister Rem is already dead.

1150
00:48:24,416 --> 00:48:26,458
What can you do by learning
anything now?

1151
00:48:26,541 --> 00:48:27,791
It's way too late for that!

1152
00:48:27,875 --> 00:48:29,791
- I won't make any cool
statements about what

1153
00:48:29,875 --> 00:48:31,375
I'll be able to do.

1154
00:48:31,458 --> 00:48:34,291
After all, this is what happened
when I couldn't do anything.

1155
00:48:34,375 --> 00:48:37,041
I know better than anyone
that my words aren't convincing

1156
00:48:37,125 --> 00:48:38,166
in the least.

1157
00:48:38,250 --> 00:48:40,291
But I do remember.

1158
00:48:40,375 --> 00:48:43,333
I know parts of you two
that you've forgotten.

1159
00:48:43,416 --> 00:48:44,541
- What are you saying?

1160
00:48:44,625 --> 00:48:46,416
What is it you think you know
about Rem and me?

1161
00:48:46,500 --> 00:48:47,916
- Don't get me wrong.

1162
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:49,500
'Cause in the grand scheme
of things,

1163
00:48:49,583 --> 00:48:51,041
what I know doesn't
really matter.

1164
00:48:51,125 --> 00:48:52,333
But it does to me,

1165
00:48:52,416 --> 00:48:55,250
and you have no idea
what it is, do you?

1166
00:48:55,333 --> 00:48:56,458
- Tell me.

1167
00:48:56,541 --> 00:48:59,000
- [inhales deeply]

1168
00:48:59,083 --> 00:49:01,083
I care for all of you!

1169
00:49:01,166 --> 00:49:03,708
Every one of you means
the world to me!

1170
00:49:05,041 --> 00:49:06,291
[grunts]
- [gasps]

1171
00:49:06,375 --> 00:49:07,916
Wait!

1172
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,916
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

1173
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:18,041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1174
00:49:29,958 --> 00:49:31,500
- [grunts]

1175
00:49:32,625 --> 00:49:34,958
This is something only I can do!

1176
00:49:35,041 --> 00:49:38,625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1177
00:49:38,708 --> 00:49:42,625
<i>- I'm going to kill you!</i>

1178
00:49:42,708 --> 00:49:47,250
- I'm going to save you!

1179
00:49:53,958 --> 00:49:56,833
<i>[MYTH&ROID's "STYX HELIX"</i>

1180
00:49:56,916 --> 00:50:04,000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1181
00:50:10,750 --> 00:50:15,333
<i>- ♪ Oh please don't let me die</i>
<i>Waiting for your touch ♪</i>

1182
00:50:15,416 --> 00:50:18,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1183
00:50:18,833 --> 00:50:23,250
<i>♪ No don't give up on life</i>
<i>This endless dead end ♪</i>

1184
00:50:23,333 --> 00:50:26,583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1185
00:50:26,666 --> 00:50:29,583
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

1186
00:50:29,666 --> 00:50:36,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1187
00:50:50,625 --> 00:50:51,708
<i>♪ I wish I was there ♪</i>

1188
00:50:51,791 --> 00:50:53,916
<i>♪ Oh please don't let me die ♪</i>

1189
00:50:54,000 --> 00:50:55,916
<i>♪ Waiting for your touch ♪</i>

1190
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:58,916
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

1191
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:05,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1192
00:51:05,625 --> 00:51:07,166
<i>♪ Restart ♪</i>

1193
00:51:07,250 --> 00:51:09,625
<i>♪ No don't give up on life ♪</i>

1194
00:51:09,708 --> 00:51:11,750
<i>♪ This endless dead end ♪</i>

1195
00:51:11,833 --> 00:51:14,708
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

1196
00:51:14,791 --> 00:51:21,500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1197
00:51:21,583 --> 00:51:25,416
<i>♪ For now I'll see you off ♪</i>

1198
00:51:25,500 --> 00:51:27,250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1199
00:51:27,333 --> 00:51:30,625
<i>♪ And we'll die</i>
<i>Waiting for a new day ♪</i>

1200
00:51:30,708 --> 00:51:33,625
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

1201
00:51:33,708 --> 00:51:35,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1202
00:51:35,250 --> 00:51:38,458
<i>♪ And we'll start waiting</i>
<i>for a new day ♪</i>

1203
00:51:38,541 --> 00:51:39,791
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

